          <h3 id="bridge-setup">Bridge Setup</h3>
          <p>Link a Discord guild to a Stoat server, then bridge individual channels.</p>

          <h4>Step 1 — Link Servers</h4>
          <p>On Stoat, a server admin generates a one-time claim code:</p>
          <div class="code-block"><pre><code>!stoatcord code</code></pre></div>
          <p>On Discord, an admin claims it and runs the migration wizard:</p>
          <div class="code-block"><pre><code>/migrate claim_code:ABC123</code></pre></div>
          <p>This creates matching channels and roles on Stoat. Options:</p>
          <div class="docs-table-wrap">
            <table class="docs-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>mode</code></td><td><code>missing</code> (default), <code>full</code>, <code>roles</code>, or <code>categories</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>dry_run</code></td><td>Preview without making changes</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>include_snapshot</code></td><td>Post full server data to #migration-log</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>include_media</code></td><td>Upload server icon, banner, emoji images</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h4>Step 2 — Link Channels</h4>
          <p>In each Discord channel you want to bridge:</p>
          <div class="code-block"><pre><code>/link stoat_channel_id:01ABC123DEF456</code></pre></div>
          <p>Messages, edits, deletes, reactions, typing indicators, and channel metadata changes sync bidirectionally.</p>
          <div class="code-block"><pre><code><span class="code-comment"># Check what's linked</span>
/status

<span class="code-comment"># Remove a channel bridge</span>
/unlink</code></pre></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Archive Migration -->
        <div class="docs-block">
          <h3 id="archive">Archive &amp; History Migration</h3>
          <p>Export Discord channel history and optionally import it into a Stoat channel.</p>

          <h4>Discord Slash Commands</h4>
          <div class="code-block"><pre><code><span class="code-comment"># Export + import in one step</span>
/archive start stoat_channel_id:01ABC123DEF456

<span class="code-comment"># Export only (no import)</span>
/archive start

<span class="code-comment"># Check job status</span>
/archive status

<span class="code-comment"># Pause / resume a running job</span>
/archive pause job_id:abc123
/archive resume job_id:abc123</code></pre></div>
          <div class="docs-table-wrap">
            <table class="docs-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>stoat_channel_id</code></td><td>Target Stoat channel (omit for export-only)</td></tr>
